\fs36\cf1 Experimental FROG Trace\plain\fs24 
\par \pard \fs20 
\par The "Experimental FROG Trace" Data Source option allows the use of experimentally generated FROG traces as the target trace.  
\par 
\par \{bmc bm4.SHG\}
\par 
\par Selecting Experimental FROG Trace will present the user with five tabs that can be used to control the execution of the FROG algorithm.
\par \fs24 
\par \pard\li715\fi-355 \uldb \fs20 Exp. Data\plain\fs20 {\v Experimental_Data_Tab} - sets the options for reading in the experimental FROG trace, its calibrations, etc.
\par 
\par \uldb Marginals\plain\fs20 {\v Marginals} - sets the input files necessary for calculating the frequency marginal, for comparison against the frequency marginal of the experimental trace.
\par 
\par \uldb Outputs\plain\fs20 {\v Outputs_Tab} - selects the directory for the \uldb output files\plain\fs20 {\v Output_Files} of the program.
\par 
\par \uldb First Guess\plain\fs20 {\v First_Guess_Field} - selects the field to be used as the starting field for the retrieval.
\par 
\par \uldb Strategies\plain\fs20 {\v Strategies_Tab} - controls the strategies used by the FROG retrieval algorithm.\fs24 
\par \pard \fs20 
\par After the OK button is pressed, the experimental data is read into the program and the \uldb Raw Data\plain\fs20 {\v Raw_Data_Window} screen appears.
