\fs36\cf1 FROG Pulse Retrieval Windows\plain\fs24 
\par \pard \fs20 
\par When retrieving a pulse, the program presents several screens that allow the user to monitor the progress of the algorithm.
\par 
\par \{bmc bm8.SHG\}
\par 
\par The windows include:
\par \fs24 
\par \pard\li715\fi-355 \uldb \fs20 Target FROG Trace\plain\fs20 {\v FROG_Trace_Windows}: the original FROG trace that the algorithm is trying to match.
\par 
\par \uldb Retrieved FROG Trace\plain\fs20 {\v FROG_Trace_Windows}: the FROG trace of the current retrieved field.
\par 
\par \uldb Electric Field\plain\fs20 {\v Electric_Field_and_Spectrum_Windows}: shows the intensity and phase of the retrieved and original (if available) electric fields in the time domain.
\par 
\par \uldb Spectrum\plain\fs20 {\v Electric_Field_and_Spectrum_Windows}: shows the intensity and phase of the retrieved and original (if available) electric fields in the frequency domain.\fs24 
\par \fs20 
\par \uldb Algorithm Control\plain\fs20 {\v Algorithm_Control}: controls the starting, stopping, and pausing of the algorithm.
\par \pard\li715\fi-355 
\par \uldb FROG Error Graph\plain\fs20 {\v FROG_Error_Graph}: plots the FROG error versus iteration.
\par 
\par \uldb Results\plain\fs20 {\v Results_Window}: displays the widths and time-bandwidth products of the original pulse (if applicable) and the retrieved pulse.
