\par \fs20 
\par For example, for a 64 X 64 trace, \i M\plain\fs20  = 5.3.  This means that a pulse with a 100 fs FWHM should be sampled every 19 fs.
\par \pard 
\par For a pulse with Gaussian intensity in the frequency domain, the maximum value for the time step is\fs24 
\par \f4\fs20 \{bmc bm11.WMF\}\f2\fs24 
\par \fs20 
