\fs36\cf1 Generate From Theory\plain\fs24 
\par \pard \fs20 
\par When "Generate From Theory" is selected as the data source, parameters describing an electric field can be input into the program.  The FROG program will then generate an electric field from these parameters.
\par 
\par \{bmc bm15.SHG\}
\par 
\par There are four tabs that are available to control the operation of the FROG algorithm when Generate From Theory is selected:
\par \fs24 
\par \pard\li715\fi-355 \uldb \fs20 Initial Field\plain\fs20 {\v Initial_Field_Generation} - used to input the parameters that govern the generation of the initial electric field.\fs24 
\par \pard 
\par \pard\li715\fi-355 \uldb \fs20 Outputs\plain\fs20 {\v Outputs_Tab} - selects the directory for the output files of the program.
\par 
\par \uldb First Guess\plain\fs20 {\v First_Guess_Field} - selects the field to be used as the starting field for the retrieval.
\par 
\par \uldb Strategies\plain\fs20 {\v Strategies_Tab} - controls the strategies used by the FROG retrieval algorithm.\fs24 
\par \pard \fs20 
