\fs36\cf1 Results Window\plain\fs24 
\par \pard 
\par \fs20 While the algorithm is retrieving a pulse, the Results window appears.  This window displays the various widths and time-bandwidth products of the pulses.  For retrievals with an original electric field that is known (Theoretical or Read-in \uldb Data Sources\plain\fs20 {\v Data_Source}), the results for the original field are shown as soon as the field is specified.  The parameters of the retrieved field are calculated after the Stop button in \uldb Algorithm Control\plain\fs20 {\v Algorithm_Control} is pressed.
