\par In practice, division of the fields in this manner often yields spurious results, especially in the wings of the pulse.  However, if the test pulse is strong enough to measure a TADPOLE spectrum, one can usually also measure the spectrum of the pulse.  The TADPOLE algorithm can be configured to use the experimentally measured spectral intensity, rather than the one calculated from the TADPOLE data.  In this case, only the spectral phase is calculated from the TADPOLE data.\f2\fs24 
